It's seems that any viewfile macro that relies on Flash doesn't work properly across the relay between Sharepoint and Confluence.

I have a Confluence page with a powerpoint (.ppt) attachment and a flash file (.swf) with the following wiki markup:
{code}
{viewppt:test.ppt}
!test.swf!
{code}

Within Sharepoint I add a Confluence page webpart that pulls in the Confluence page described above.  The embedded flash file displays properly while the viewppt section shows a the flash logo with the message 'You need flash player installed to preview ppt and pdf files.'

Suspect trace:
http://confsharepoint/s/1722/1/1/_/download/resources/com.atlassian.confluence.extra.officeconnector:pptslideservlet/conversion/Slides.swf    400 BAD REQUEST

http://confsharepoint is my Sharepoint url.  My Confluence url is actually http://maleko:8031.  It seems that it's trying to download the result of the viewppt from the wrong url.

